{
  "texts": [
    "Scientists must develop new skills, literacy, and competency to effectively utilize AI, understanding its limitations and potential biases while leveraging its strengths to enhance their research.",
    "From this perspective, generative AI becomes part of the scientific process, not only as a tool, but as an active participant that co-evolves with human authorship.",
    "This co-evolution reflects a dynamic where both entities influence and shape each other.",
    "As scientists adapt their practices to incorporate AI, the AI itself evolves through updates and learning from its interactions with scientists.",
    "Furthermore, as scientific fields evolve, the roles of authors and AI will likely become even more intertwined, promoting ongoing dialog and adaptation within the scientific community."
  ]
}